# Contributing to SharpClaw

Thank you for your interest in contributing to SharpClaw.

By submitting any code, documentation, or other material to this repository (a "Contribution"), whether by pull request, patch, commit, or any other means, you agree to the following Contributor License Agreement ("Agreement").

1. Definitions

"Licensor" means the copyright owner of SharpClaw, identified as mkn8rn, acting as an individual or legal entity.
"You" or "Contributor" means the individual or legal entity submitting a Contribution.
"Contribution" means any original work of authorship, including code, documentation, or other material, submitted by You to the repository.

2. Copyright License Grant

You hereby grant the Licensor a perpetual, worldwide, irrevocable, royalty-free, non-exclusive, transferable, and sublicensable license to your Contribution to:

- use the Contribution for any purpose;
- reproduce, modify, adapt, and create derivative works from it;
- merge it with other works or code;
- publish, perform, and distribute it;
- sublicense it to third parties;
- sell, license, or otherwise commercially exploit it, whether as part of SharpClaw or independently;
- license or relicense it under any terms chosen by the Licensor, including but not limited to AGPL-3.0 (or any later version) and commercial proprietary licenses.

3. Patent License Grant

To the extent that You hold any patent rights that are necessarily infringed by the use, modification, or distribution of your Contribution, You hereby grant the Licensor and its sublicensees a perpetual, worldwide, irrevocable, royalty-free, non-exclusive, transferable, and sublicensable patent license to make, have made, use, offer to sell, sell, import, and otherwise exploit the Contribution.

4. Patent Retaliation

If You initiate patent litigation (including a cross-claim or counterclaim) alleging that the Contribution or SharpClaw infringes any patent, then any patent licenses granted to You under this Agreement with respect to that Contribution shall terminate as of the date such litigation is filed.

5. Moral Rights

To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, You hereby waive, or where waiver is not legally possible, agree not to assert, any moral rights or similar rights (including rights of attribution, integrity, or disclosure) in your Contribution, insofar as such rights would interfere with the exercise of the rights granted under this Agreement.

6. Representations and Warranties

You represent and warrant that:

- You are the original author of the Contribution, or You have the legal right to submit it under the terms of this Agreement;
- the Contribution does not infringe or misappropriate the rights of any third party;
- the Contribution does not include material subject to third-party licenses or obligations that would conflict with the rights granted under this Agreement;
- if the Contribution was created in the course of employment or under a contract, You have obtained all necessary permissions to grant the rights described herein.

7. No Obligation

Nothing in this Agreement obligates the Licensor to include, distribute, or continue to use any Contribution. All Contributions are provided "as is", without warranty of any kind.

8. Acceptance Mechanism

All Contributions must be submitted via pull request.
Each pull request must include the following statement in its description:

"I confirm that I have read and agree to the terms in CONTRIBUTING.md."

Pull requests that do not contain this confirmation may be rejected without review.

9. Governing Law and Jurisdiction

This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the Republic of Croatia.
The courts of the Republic of Croatia shall have exclusive jurisdiction over any disputes arising out of or in connection with this Agreement.

10. Entire Agreement

This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement between You and the Licensor concerning Contributions and supersedes any prior agreements or understandings relating to the subject matter herein.

If You do not agree to these terms, do not submit Contributions to this repository.
